content:
KeyValueStoreReplica.OnCopyComplete Method

Definition

Namespace:
System.Fabric
Assembly:
System.Fabric.dll

In this Article

Called by the system on secondary replicas when they have finished building from the primary and are ready to start applying replication operations.

This method will only be called on secondary replicas if the KeyValueStoreReplica object was constructed with a valid KeyValueStoreReplica.SecondaryNotificationMode parameter.

protected virtual void OnCopyComplete (System.Fabric.KeyValueStoreEnumerator enumerator);
Parameters
enumerator
KeyValueStoreEnumerator

The enumerator used to read data on the secondary.

Remarks

The object can be used to read data on the secondary within the context of this method before any replication operations are applied. The object is no longer valid after this method returns and cannot be used outside the context of this method. The application must take care to complete this callback in a timely manner since replication operations are being queued on the secondary replica and will not start getting applied until this method returns. The object is backed by a single underlying local transaction and is not thread-safe.
